name: Georgetown Liquor Company
description: Punk bar for drinks and local beers, serving an all-vegan menu of sandwiches, salads & sides. Off the beaten path and nestled right next to the train tracks, this popular local hangout first opened in January 2006. After closing in September 2020, it was reopened December 2020 under new ownership. Retaining a sense of community and punk rock vibe, it is being reopened by local Georgetown resident and long time GLC patron (and former co-owner of famed Highline Bar) Alan Threewit. Out with the old and in with the new. While keeping in the GLC tradition in some ways, expect a revamped image and theme along with a new and improved all-vegan food and drink menu. We take pride in our faux meats, cheeses, and sauces; all of which are made from scratch, in-house. All of our food is made to order and with lots of love.

name: Seattle Vacation Home: Roy Street Cottage - 3 bedroom single family home with
description:
The space
This single story home is located on a quiet residential street just two blocks from the heart of Madison Valley. Enter into a cozy living area furnished with a sleeper sofa and large TV with a complete DirecTV package.  The kitchen was recently updated and features new appliances and granite countertops.  A small dining room has a table that seats 8.

Walk down the hallway and you'll come to the three bedrooms.  They are furnished as follows:
- Bedroom 1: King bed
- Bedroom 2: Queen bed and twin bed
- Bedroom 3: Queen bed

A full bathroom is shared by the three bedrooms.  The home is equipped with a full-sized washer/dryer.

Guest access
Access to the home is provided without a cumbersome lock box or key exchange. Instead, you will choose a 4 digit code, and the electronic lock to the home will be programmed work your code for the duration of your stay.

You will have access to the entire home, including off street parking. 

Interaction with guests
Your hosts, Andy and Lynne, live in the neighborhood. We are here to welcome you and help you with any of your needs during your stay. We are happy to offer you advice for sightseeing and restaurant recommendations.

Guests will receive, in advance, our comprehensive homemade visitors' guide to Seattle, packed with our personal recommendations for dining, activities, and much more.

Do you plan to cook during your stay? By special advanced arrangement (depending on availability), we will fulfill your grocery list and have your home stocked for your arrival.
The neighborhood
This home is central to everything Madison Valley has to offer: great restaurants, parks, hiking, supermarkets, day spas, and more. Your hosts made Madison Valley their home when first settling in Seattle ... and haven't looked back since.

We love walking the streets of this neighborhood, and we will gladly suggest fun walks depending on your interests. Stroll to the beach at Madison Park. Walk by multi-million dollar estates. Discover hidden neighborhood gems such as the farmhouse with horses in the yard and the home that doubles as an eclectic art studio and antique truck gallery. Take a walk through the fabled Arboretum to Lake Washington.

Once you have worked up your appetite, enjoy the countless restaurants that Madison Valley ("Little Paris") has to offer. In addition to French gems, try our favorite tapas restaurant or the best Japanese food east of Tokyo. Take your morning coffee in one of numerous bakeries. Or opt for Thai, pan-Asian, craft pizza, Tex-Mex or more.

Our home provides easy access to Downtown (Pikes Place Market, Seattle Art Museum, Seattle Great Wheel), Seattle Center (Space Needle, Chihuly Glass Museum), South Lake Union (MOHAI), University of Washington, and Capitol Hill. All are accessible by car, bus (numerous bus lines a few blocks from home), or for the adventurous, by foot.

If all of this touring (and eating) has you tired, pamper yourself with a visit to a day spa or nail salon. There are several of each within a few blocks of home, and we are happy to point you in the right direction.

Seattle Vacation Home LLC manages this home on behalf of the owner/license holder.
This home has a maximum sleeping capacity of 9.  However, Seattle regulations state that no more than 8 *unrelated* guests are permitted per booking.  Groups greater in size than 8 will need to affirm that there are no more than 8 unrelated individuals in the group.

To respect our neighbors, this home may use internal NoiseAware sensors.  These devices do not record audio within the home, but will alert Seattle Vacation Home when the volume exceeds a level that threatens neighborhood tranquility.  We may also use EXTERIOR security cameras to promote the safety of our guests, neighbors and team members.
